{\an1}{\pos(211.5,260.1)}安德伍德拿下俄亥俄
康威将认输

17
00:02:41,650 --> 00:02:45,220
将军竟然说要杀死总统
The general talked about killing the president.

18
00:02:45,220 --> 00:02:47,790
再加上康威在飞机上的爆发
That, along with Conway's outburst on the plane--

19
00:02:47,790 --> 00:02:49,160
这么说好像夸大了实际情况
That sounds worse than it was.

20
00:02:49,160 --> 00:02:51,460
不  实际情况就是这么严重
No, that sounds exactly as bad as it was.

21
00:02:51,470 --> 00:02:53,160
让我觉得惊讶的是
What's surprising to me is...

22
00:02:53,160 --> 00:02:54,890
选举团队竟然应对不过来
the campaign couldn't get their hands around this.

23
00:02:54,890 --> 00:02:57,100
哈里·马歇尔已经很厉害了
I mean, Harry Marshall is as good as they come, but--

24
00:02:57,110 --> 00:02:59,840
他们先是否认  接着又模棱两可
First they denied, and then they equivocated--

25
00:02:59,840 --> 00:03:01,400
这简直太荒唐了
I mean, that's just, like, ridiculous.

26
00:03:01,400 --> 00:03:02,270
你站出来
You just come out,

27
00:03:02,270 --> 00:03:03,940
"我道歉  我们说错话了"
"I apologize. We misspoke."

28
00:03:03,940 --> 00:03:05,150
所有人都知道这套路
Everybody knows the drill here.

29
00:03:05,150 --> 00:03:06,840
共和党人也没有冲过去帮他们
And it's not like the Republicans rushed in

30
00:03:06,840 --> 00:03:08,570
力挽狂澜
to save the day either.

31
00:03:08,570 --> 00:03:10,870
-完全不谈正题  -他们默不作声
- Off message throughout. - They got quiet.

32
00:03:10,870 --> 00:03:13,160
这一点我怎么也想不通
Which I will never understand.

33
00:03:13,160 --> 00:03:16,770
威尔·康威可是党内冉冉升起的新星
Will Conway was a rising star in the party.

34
00:03:16,770 --> 00:03:20,030
怎么能跟安德伍德政治机器相匹敌呢
Look, it's hard to compete with the Underwood machine.

35
00:03:20,030 --> 00:03:23,320
天啊  我们别再说这些"阴谋占领"的疯话了
God. Let's not do the whole "black helicopters" crazy stuff.

36
00:03:23,330 --> 00:03:23,900
太荒唐了
It's ridiculous.

37
00:03:23,910 --> 00:03:26,580
我们得接受安德伍德赢得大选这一事实
Look, we need to accept Underwood won the election.

38
00:03:26,580 --> 00:03:28,490
公众得接受这个结果  继续前进
People need to accept the outcome and move on.

39
00:03:28,500 --> 00:03:29,960
我同意范的观点
I'm gonna agree with Van.

40
00:03:29,960 --> 00:03:33,630
我觉得我们应该感激宪法
I think we need to take a moment to appreciate the Constitution.

41
00:03:33,630 --> 00:03:34,520
它会弯折[妥协]It bent,

42
00:03:34,520 --> 00:03:36,700
-但不会折断[毁坏]  -说得没错
- but it never broke. - That's right.

43
00:03:36,700 --> 00:03:38,390
我们都知道  到最后
And in the end, as we all know,

44
00:03:38,390 --> 00:03:40,420
还是由选举人团决定
it came down to the Electoral College.

45
00:03:41,000 --> 00:03:43,910
你不用说那句话  州长
You don't have to say the words, Governor.

46
00:03:46,940 --> 00:03:48,010
我应该说
I think I do.

47
00:03:51,840 --> 00:03:54,460
恭喜  当选总统先生
Congratulations, Mr. President Elect.

48
00:03:56,020 --> 00:03:57,860
这次没有稿子吗
There's no script for this one?

49
00:03:57,860 --> 00:03:59,540
国家第一  先生
Country first, sir.

50
00:03:59,710 --> 00:04:01,710
我很高兴你这么说  威尔
I'm glad to hear you say that, Will.

51
00:04:01,710 --> 00:04:05,740
我想帮这个国家愈合
I want to start to help the country heal again.

52
00:04:05,740 --> 00:04:06,760
说完了吗
Are we done?

53
00:04:07,250 --> 00:04:10,330
说完了  但是威尔
We are done. But Will...

54
00:04:12,520 --> 00:04:15,360
我很想向国家展示
I would very much like to show the country

55
00:04:15,360 --> 00:04:17,870
我们两党可以齐心协作
that our two parties can work together.

56
00:04:17,870 --> 00:04:20,500
我希望你考虑
So I was hoping that you might consider

57
00:04:20,610 --> 00:04:24,300
做我的运输部长
becoming my transportation secretary.

58
00:04:24,740 --> 00:04:26,630
如果你同意加入我的内阁
I think it would send a powerful message

59
00:04:26,630 --> 00:04:29,230
会发出一个强有力的信号
if you agreed to join my cabinet.

60
00:04:29,920 --> 00:04:31,050
你觉得我能
You think I'd...

61
00:04:32,300 --> 00:04:36,250
当好运输部长吗
make a good... transportation secretary?

62
00:04:36,450 --> 00:04:37,480
没错
Yes.

63
00:04:37,790 --> 00:04:40,340
这是开给无名议员的条件
That's what you give the congressman from nowhere.

64
00:04:40,470 --> 00:04:41,220
我会拒绝的
I'll be declining.

65
00:04:41,220 --> 00:04:43,000
听到你这么说真是太遗憾了  威尔
Well, I'm so sorry to hear that, Will.

66
00:04:43,000 --> 00:04:45,300
我想祝你一切顺利
And I wanted to wish you the very best.

67
00:04:45,300 --> 00:04:47,920
去你的  去你的祝福
You and your wishes can go fuck yourselves!

68
00:05:00,800 --> 00:05:01,920
我现在做什么
What do I do now?

69
00:05:02,410 --> 00:05:03,540
所有人都以为威尔会赢
...everyone thought it would happen.

70
00:05:03,540 --> 00:05:05,490
没人想到安德伍德还能赢
No one thought that Underwood would win again...

71
00:05:06,550 --> 00:05:07,560
我不知道
I don't know.

72
00:05:13,090 --> 00:05:15,630
承认失败从来都不容易
Acknowledging defeat is never easy.

73
00:05:15,630 --> 00:05:19,170
在公众面前承认更是无比煎熬
Doing it in public is a living hell.

74
00:05:19,830 --> 00:05:21,820
起码媒体喜欢他
Well, at least the cameras like him.

75
00:05:30,680 --> 00:05:32,550
我看着满意吗
Do I look satisfied?

76
00:05:33,540 --> 00:05:36,130
你看着还算满意
You look somewhat satisfied.

77
00:05:36,130 --> 00:05:37,790
-好  -"好"可不够
- Good. - Not good.

78
00:05:37,790 --> 00:05:39,890
弗兰西斯  享受这一刻吧
Francis, enjoy this moment.

79
00:05:40,450 --> 00:05:43,970
-这是你应得的  -是"我们"吧
- You deserve it. - You mean "we."

80
00:05:44,880 --> 00:05:47,270
我们成功到达另一边了
We made it to the other side.

81
00:05:47,900 --> 00:05:49,030
是啊
Yes.

82
00:05:50,390 --> 00:05:52,940
但另一边有什么
But what is on the other side?

83
00:05:53,490 --> 00:05:54,560
胜利
Victory.

84
00:05:55,760 --> 00:05:57,580
稍带点失败的气息
With a whiff of defeat.

85
00:05:59,120 --> 00:06:00,740
花了好久才走到这一步
It's taken a long time to get here,

86
00:06:00,740 --> 00:06:01,800
但我们到了
but we're here.

87
00:06:02,000 --> 00:06:03,540
干杯  弗兰西斯
Cheers, Francis.

88
00:06:04,220 --> 00:06:06,670
今后一切都会变得容易
Everything gets easier from now on.

89
00:06:22,300 --> 00:06:23,350
他们准备好了
They're ready for you.

90
00:06:28,390 --> 00:06:30,700
-汉娜  -我不想去
- Hannah. - I don't want to go.

91
00:06:46,640 --> 00:06:47,710
不
No.

92
00:06:54,940 --> 00:06:55,860
好吧
Fine.

93
00:06:57,380 --> 00:06:58,680
那我自己去吧
I'll do it on my own.

94
00:06:59,050 --> 00:07:01,070
要知道  这是个重要时刻
I'm gonna say, this is a crucial moment.

95
00:07:01,070 --> 00:07:02,000
对你们两个都是
For both of you.

96
00:07:02,010 --> 00:07:03,170
看你们如何应对
How you handle tonight.

97
00:07:03,170 --> 00:07:04,710
党抛弃了我
The party abandoned me.

98
00:07:05,820 --> 00:07:06,930
你的党
Your party.

99
00:07:07,520 --> 00:07:09,400
我不是共和党  威尔
I'm not the Republican Party, Will.

100
00:07:10,940 --> 00:07:12,370
我只为候选人效力
I work for candidates.

101
00:07:13,820 --> 00:07:15,110
我为你效力
I worked for you.

102
00:07:16,480 --> 00:07:18,250
听好  你输了
Listen, you lost.

103
00:07:18,250 --> 00:07:19,430
但还有一多半国民
But more than half the country

104
00:07:19,430 --> 00:07:21,630
仍认为你是他们的总统
still considers you their president.

105
00:07:22,050 --> 00:07:23,010
你必须要面对他们
This is what's required.

106
00:07:23,010 --> 00:07:24,710
走出去  发表讲话
Go down there, give your speech.

107
00:07:27,830 --> 00:07:28,960
认输吧
Concede.

108
00:08:02,580 --> 00:08:03,840
{\pos(222,73.8)}国务卿  华盛顿

109
00:08:05,920 --> 00:08:09,970
{\an7}{\pos(47.7,105.75)}尊敬的总统先生
我谨辞去第68任国务卿职务

110
00:08:09,970 --> 00:08:14,010
{\an7}{\pos(36.3,245.25)}此致
凯瑟琳·杜兰特

111
00:08:46,970 --> 00:08:50,180
我正式接受各位的辞呈
As I accept all of your letters of resignation

112
00:08:50,200 --> 00:08:52,700
并解散我的旧内阁
and dissolve my old cabinet,

113
00:08:52,710 --> 00:08:56,760
然后我想欢迎在座各位加入我的新内阁
I wanna welcome each and every one of you to my new cabinet.

114
00:09:00,660 --> 00:09:03,600
-恭喜你  总统先生  -谢谢  凯茜
- Congratulations, Mr. President. - Thank you, Cathy.

115
00:09:03,890 --> 00:09:06,620
我尤其想感谢我的妻子
And I especially wanna thank my wife.

116
00:09:08,100 --> 00:09:09,820
副总统女士
Madam Vice President...

117
00:09:10,260 --> 00:09:14,100
感谢你对我长期坚定的支持
thank you for your unending and unwavering support.

118
00:09:14,100 --> 00:09:19,060
这一个月来  你的坚强领导维持了国家的运作
Your steady hand kept this country running this past month.

119
00:09:19,510 --> 00:09:22,160
我欠她太多  多到我无法想象
I owe her more than I can possibly fathom.

120
00:09:22,320 --> 00:09:23,920
而她也欠我
And she owes me.

121
00:09:24,840 --> 00:09:28,940
不对  你一直在我身边支持着我
Not true. You were with me all the way.

122
00:09:29,840 --> 00:09:32,730
作为合法当选总统
I would like to make my first 100 days

123
00:09:32,730 --> 00:09:36,840
我希望我的头一百天能取得尽可能多的成绩
as the duly elected president as productive as possible.

124
00:09:36,840 --> 00:09:38,710
当然  挑战还是很多的
Of course, there are many challenges.

125
00:09:39,000 --> 00:09:40,070
提振经济
Shoring up the economy,

126
00:09:40,070 --> 00:09:42,830
保护我国不受哈里发国攻击
securing our nation from ICO

127
00:09:42,830 --> 00:09:44,340
还要降低失业率
and reducing unemployment.

128
00:09:44,340 --> 00:09:46,360
但我们面对的最艰巨的问题
But the biggest challenge that we face,

129
00:09:46,360 --> 00:09:49,720
也是我最需要各位通力协助的挑战
and the one that I'm going to need all of your help on,

130
00:09:49,780 --> 00:09:51,910
就是重新团结全国
is reuniting a country

131
00:09:51,990 --> 00:09:55,200
弥合这个国家前所未有的裂痕
that has never been more divided than it is today.

132
00:09:55,810 --> 00:09:58,450
我相信我们可以迎难而上
I believe we can meet this challenge,

133
00:09:58,450 --> 00:10:00,880
而我需要各位的帮助
and that's where I'm gonna need all of your help.

134
00:10:00,880 --> 00:10:04,120
所以今天我们就开始治愈国家
So let's let the healing begin today

135
00:10:04,430 --> 00:10:06,420
共同创造历史吧
and let's make history together.

136
00:10:06,530 --> 00:10:08,940
感谢你们长久的辛勤奉献
I thank you all for your continued service.

137
00:10:08,940 --> 00:10:10,550
现在回去工作吧
Now let's get back to work.

138
00:10:27,890 --> 00:10:28,920
我需要一分钟
I need a minute.

139
00:10:30,430 --> 00:10:31,420
我想我们应该早做打算
I think we should see what we can do

140
00:10:31,420 --> 00:10:34,180
把厄舍赶走
about making Usher persona non grata.

141
00:10:34,690 --> 00:10:36,540
现在开战不合适吧
I don't think that's wise to start a war.

142
00:10:36,540 --> 00:10:38,120
我们才刚刚拿下白宫
We've just won the White House.

143
00:10:38,120 --> 00:10:40,200
现在才是出手的最佳时机
This is exactly when we should strike.

144
00:10:40,200 --> 00:10:41,730
只有现在我们才有足够的政治资本
This is a moment that we have the political capital...

145
00:10:41,730 --> 00:10:44,610
厄舍必须小心处理
Usher needs to be managed carefully.

146
00:10:45,030 --> 00:10:46,230
总统先生
Mr. President?

147
00:10:46,670 --> 00:10:47,940
喘口气吧  道格
Take a breath, Doug.

148
00:10:47,940 --> 00:10:49,950
我们才刚刚站稳脚跟
We've only just landed on our feet here.

149
00:10:49,950 --> 00:10:51,760
先生  副总统女士
Sir, Madam Vice President,

150
00:10:51,760 --> 00:10:54,520
过去在众议院  这种人就是重点打击对象
this is the type of person that we used to crucify in the House.

151
00:10:54,520 --> 00:10:57,340
但现在我们不在众议院  我们在白宫
Yes, but we're not in the House now. We're here.

152
00:10:57,340 --> 00:10:59,030
我们还有一整个任期呢
We have a full term ahead of us.

153
00:10:59,030 --> 00:11:00,520
我们肯定会取得
There's gonna be a great deal

154
00:11:00,520 --> 00:11:01,920
非常多的成就
that we're gonna be able to accomplish,

155
00:11:01,920 --> 00:11:03,140
咱们三个合作
the three of us.

156
00:11:03,810 --> 00:11:05,400
感谢您的器重  先生
I appreciate that, sir.

157
00:11:05,960 --> 00:11:08,510
但是马克·厄舍早晚会变成麻烦的
But Mark Usher will become a problem.

158
00:11:08,510 --> 00:11:11,970
每个人早晚都会变成麻烦
Well, everyone becomes a problem, eventually.

159
00:11:16,070 --> 00:11:17,220
莉安出局了
LeAnn's out.

160
00:11:17,420 --> 00:11:18,370
什么
What?

161
00:11:21,370 --> 00:11:22,210
为什么
Why?

162
00:11:27,780 --> 00:11:28,840
她搞砸了
She screwed up.

163
00:11:29,980 --> 00:11:31,770
有什么需要我准备的吗
Well, is it something I need to get ready for?

164
00:11:31,770 --> 00:11:34,150
安德伍德夫妇希望间接处理她
The Underwoods want this handled indirectly.

165
00:11:35,050 --> 00:11:36,980
所以我们具体该说什么
So what exactly are we saying?

166
00:11:37,180 --> 00:11:38,680
她被赶走了
She's being pushed out.

167
00:11:39,070 --> 00:11:41,020
好  但是选举结束了
Okay, but the campaign's over.

168
00:11:41,020 --> 00:11:42,750
还有必要对外说什么吗
Is it necessary to say anything?

169
00:11:42,850 --> 00:11:44,650
我们需要撇清本届政府与她
We need to distance this administration

170
00:11:44,660 --> 00:11:45,940
和她工作的关系
from her and her work.

171
00:11:45,950 --> 00:11:47,530
还有她的策略
Her tactics.

172
00:11:49,120 --> 00:11:50,630
得装成是泄露出去的
So it needs to be a leak.

173
00:11:50,960 --> 00:11:52,860
泄露给不喜欢我们的人
Reach out to the people who don't like us.

174
00:11:52,860 --> 00:11:54,430
他们肯定乐意爆料
They'll be prime to go with it.

175
00:11:54,630 --> 00:11:56,380
等我们回应的时候
Okay, so when we respond...

176
00:11:56,380 --> 00:11:58,160
-是公开还是  -公开
- On the record or... - On.

177
00:12:01,490 --> 00:12:02,490
她做了什么
What did she do?

178
00:12:03,360 --> 00:12:05,460
她展现出了很差的判断力
She showed some very poor judgment.

179
00:12:06,620 --> 00:12:08,540
我相信你会谨慎的
I'm trusting you to be discreet.

180
00:12:10,150 --> 00:12:11,450
我们赢了  赛斯
We won, Seth.

181
00:12:11,740 --> 00:12:13,300
需要做出一些改变
Changes need to be made.

182
00:12:15,850 --> 00:12:17,360
你知道我已经远离政治了
You know I'm off politics.

183
00:12:17,360 --> 00:12:18,910
你来找我  我真的很惊讶
Surprised you reached out to me.

184
00:12:18,910 --> 00:12:20,980
你是一位非常受人尊敬的记者
You're a highly-respected journalist.

185
00:12:21,500 --> 00:12:23,940
就是来参加就职典礼和舞会而已
Just here for the inauguration and the parties.

186
00:12:25,690 --> 00:12:28,210
我想你已经听说了  我被赶走了
So I imagine you've heard that I'm on the outs.

187
00:12:29,020 --> 00:12:30,870
他们没有说出全部实情
They're not telling the whole story.

188
00:12:32,500 --> 00:12:33,580
发生了什么
So what happened?

189
00:12:33,740 --> 00:12:35,230
我有个熟人
An acquaintance of mine

190
00:12:35,230 --> 00:12:37,590
从国安局偷了机密文件
stole classified documents from the NSA

191
00:12:37,590 --> 00:12:39,220
去了俄罗斯
and took off to Russia.

192
00:12:40,470 --> 00:12:41,980
他们因为这件事责怪我
They're blaming me for it.

193
00:12:44,140 --> 00:12:45,970
你这个熟人带走的是什么
What did this acquaintance take?

194
00:12:46,930 --> 00:12:50,520
问题就是这个  我也不知道
That's just the thing. I have no idea.

195
00:12:51,120 --> 00:12:53,260
要是你能找到他  跟他谈谈
If you could find him, talk to him,

196
00:12:53,260 --> 00:12:56,180
他会告诉你  我和这事一点关系都没有
he would tell you that I had nothing to do with this.

197
00:13:02,780 --> 00:13:04,540
他是谁  他叫什么
Who is he? What's his name?

198
00:13:06,650 --> 00:13:07,980
艾丹·麦卡伦
Aidan Macallan.

199
00:13:08,080 --> 00:13:11,060
他会跟你谈的  他尊重你
He'll talk to you. He respects you.

200
00:13:13,180 --> 00:13:15,010
告诉他我现在没事
Tell him that I'm okay.

201
00:13:16,270 --> 00:13:17,970
以后也会没事的
That I'm going to be okay.

202
00:13:19,540 --> 00:13:21,440
我坚信派遣地面部队
I'm a firm believer in boots on the ground.

203
00:13:21,440 --> 00:13:23,830
我们就是为了石油去的  别装了
Well, we're there for the oil. Let's not pretend.

204
00:13:23,830 --> 00:13:27,290
我不否认保护原油供应的重要性
I'm not denying how crucial it is to protect the oil supply.

205
00:13:27,290 --> 00:13:29,000
但由我们来盯住
But it's in the world's best interest

206
00:13:29,000 --> 00:13:30,930
对整个世界都好
that we're the ones keeping an eye on it.

207
00:13:30,940 --> 00:13:33,560
-盯住世界还是石油  -都是
- On the world or the oil? - Both.

208
00:13:34,500 --> 00:13:37,600
难怪你对南极那么感兴趣
Well, that explains your strong interest in Antarctica.

209
00:13:37,600 --> 00:13:41,140
我确实关注事情和人
I do focus on things and people.

210
00:13:41,150 --> 00:13:42,480
我常会起怜惜之情
I tend to get attached,

211
00:13:42,480 --> 00:13:45,050
但我觉得这让我的工作更加出色
but I think it makes me better at what I do.

212
00:13:45,910 --> 00:13:47,590
你现在关注什么
And what are you focused on now?

213
00:13:47,590 --> 00:13:52,420
首先是佩特罗夫和艾哈迈德·艾哈迈迪
Petrov. Ahmed Al Ahmadi. To begin with.

214
00:13:57,230 --> 00:13:58,560
抱歉
I'm... I'm sorry.

215
00:14:00,700 --> 00:14:01,680
我只是
I just...

216
00:14:03,660 --> 00:14:05,100
我明天再问你的意见
I'll run this by you tomorrow.

217
00:14:06,290 --> 00:14:07,770
好  明天
Yes, tomorrow.

218
00:14:10,020 --> 00:14:11,490
抱歉打断你们了
Sorry for the interruption.

219
00:14:14,270 --> 00:14:16,020
他是我们的一个演讲撰稿人
He's one of our speechwriters.

220
00:14:16,960 --> 00:14:19,350
汤姆·耶茨很有名
Tom Yates has quite a reputation.

221
00:14:20,450 --> 00:14:22,290
要是他的书能说明什么的话
Well, if his books are any indication,

222
00:14:22,290 --> 00:14:24,180
他的生活可很精彩
he has lived quite a life.

223
00:14:24,630 --> 00:14:26,610
我爸爸也穿条纹袜
My father wore striped socks.

224
00:14:29,260 --> 00:14:32,860
你觉得总统会赞同我们的议程吗
Do you think the president will be sympathetic to our agenda?

225
00:14:33,280 --> 00:14:36,200
"我们的议程"  这么说太自负了
"Our agenda"? That's very presumptuous.

226
00:14:36,290 --> 00:14:38,080
这世界上有些地区
Well, there are regions in the world

227
00:14:38,080 --> 00:14:40,590
对我们的国家安全很重要
that are important to our national security

228
00:14:40,600 --> 00:14:42,560
我们必须保护这些地区
and they have to be protected.

229
00:14:42,570 --> 00:14:45,130
你想跟我们一起参加就职舞会吗
Would you like to join us at the inaugural ball?

230
00:14:45,190 --> 00:14:46,550
不行
Oh, no, I can't.

231
00:14:46,700 --> 00:14:49,990
只要我去舞会  就会发生可怕的事
Something terrible always happens when I go to a party.

232
00:14:52,460 --> 00:14:56,250
顺说  我丈夫不会受任何人的摆布
By the way, my husband is not managed by anyone.

233
00:14:56,250 --> 00:14:59,060
-我不是这个意思  -不是吗
- That's not what I'm asking. - Isn't it?

234
00:14:59,060 --> 00:15:01,450
我是想让你帮忙  副总统女士
I'm asking for your help, Madam Vice President.

235
00:15:02,150 --> 00:15:03,300
仅此而已
That is all.

236
00:15:08,760 --> 00:15:09,770
晚上好
Evening.

237
00:15:10,340 --> 00:15:11,400
天啊  进来吧
Oh, my God. Come in.

238
00:15:11,400 --> 00:15:13,810
抱歉  坐吧  坐吧
I'm sorry. Sit down, sit down.

239
00:15:13,810 --> 00:15:15,240
今晚不锻炼了吗
Aren't we working out tonight?

240
00:15:15,670 --> 00:15:18,180
我应该是没时间了
I just don't think I'm gonna have the time for it.

241
00:15:18,180 --> 00:15:19,990
过来坐一会儿
But come sit for a minute.

242
00:15:19,990 --> 00:15:20,850
要是你太忙的话
If you're too busy,

243
00:15:20,860 --> 00:15:21,970
-我能理解  -不  来跟我坐会儿
- I understand-- - No, no. Join me for a minute.

244
00:15:21,970 --> 00:15:23,400
我想让你听点东西
I want you to hear something.

245
00:15:32,640 --> 00:15:36,170
"这是新时代的黎明
"This is the dawn of a new era.

246
00:15:36,820 --> 00:15:38,450
这是和平的时代
It's a time for peace.

247
00:15:38,450 --> 00:15:43,000
要尊重过去  拥抱未来
A time to respect the past and embrace the future.

248
00:15:43,000 --> 00:15:44,380
要..."
A time..."

249
00:15:52,980 --> 00:15:53,970
要什么
Time to what?

250
00:15:53,970 --> 00:15:57,600
"要聆听所有声音
"A time to hear all the voices.

251
00:15:57,600 --> 00:16:00,210
因为世间最大的孤独
For there is nothing more lonely...

252
00:16:02,440 --> 00:16:04,100
恐怖
or terrifying...

253
00:16:07,110 --> 00:16:09,180
便是无人聆听"
than feeling unheard."

254
00:16:12,680 --> 00:16:14,060
你觉得怎么样
What do you think?

255
00:16:14,060 --> 00:16:16,180
有意思  我喜欢
It's interesting. I like it.

256
00:16:16,770 --> 00:16:20,170
-这是为了  -我的就职典礼  没错
- This is for... - My inauguration, yes.

257
00:16:21,180 --> 00:16:23,050
然后呢  你接下去怎么说
Where does it go from there? What do you say?

258
00:16:27,050 --> 00:16:29,390
"美国人民  我听到了你们的声音
"America, I hear you.

259
00:16:30,220 --> 00:16:32,390
无论你们是否投票给了我
Whether you voted for me or not,

260
00:16:33,000 --> 00:16:35,120
我听到了你们所有人的声音"
I hear all of you."

261
00:16:36,480 --> 00:16:39,120
你觉得我的曾曾曾祖父
Now, what do you think my great-great-great-grandfather

262
00:16:39,120 --> 00:16:41,060
会怎么评价这些
would think of all this?

263
00:16:44,100 --> 00:16:45,340
令人敬畏[非常好]
Awesome.

264
00:16:47,490 --> 00:16:49,840
-就这词原本的意思  -是啊
- In the original sense of the word. - Yeah.

265
00:16:52,130 --> 00:16:53,420
你要在这儿待多久
How long you in town for?

266
00:16:54,580 --> 00:16:56,140
实际上  今晚就走
Leaving tonight, actually.

267
00:16:56,260 --> 00:16:58,120
我以为你是来参加就职典礼的
I thought you were here for the inauguration.

268
00:16:58,120 --> 00:17:00,010
我收到了一条消息  得走了
I got a tip I have to move on.

269
00:17:01,170 --> 00:17:02,330
什么消息
What's the tip?

270
00:17:03,670 --> 00:17:06,000
咱们以前对工作谈话可是有规矩的
We used to have a rule about shoptalk.

271
00:17:06,000 --> 00:17:07,000
是吗
Did we?

272
00:17:07,560 --> 00:17:08,590
好吧
Fair enough.

273
00:17:13,200 --> 00:17:15,450
你怎么看莉安·哈维
What's your read on LeAnn Harvey?

274
00:17:16,610 --> 00:17:19,640
她很难看透  这也是我喜欢她之处
That she's hard to read. That's what I like about her.

275
00:17:19,690 --> 00:17:20,910
你信任她
You trust her?

276
00:17:23,100 --> 00:17:24,450
凯特  拜托
Kate, come on.

277
00:17:30,780 --> 00:17:32,020
你很憔悴
You look tired.

278
00:17:33,420 --> 00:17:34,880
我现在一周工作八天
I'm working eight days a week.

279
00:17:35,990 --> 00:17:37,020
你以前也总是很憔悴的样子
I mean, you always looked tired,

280
00:17:37,020 --> 00:17:40,500
但你现在的憔悴  不那么性感了
but now you look tired in a... not sexy way.

281
00:17:42,210 --> 00:17:43,700
抱歉让你失望了
Sorry to disappoint.

282
00:17:43,780 --> 00:17:45,600
其实我马上就得回去了
I actually have to get back there in a minute.

283
00:17:45,830 --> 00:17:48,270
这会儿回办公室有点晚了吧
It's little late to head back to the office, right?

284
00:17:52,380 --> 00:17:54,250
我从上周二起就一直在那边
I've been there since last Tuesday.

285
00:17:56,010 --> 00:17:56,950
说实话
Honestly...

286
00:17:58,020 --> 00:17:59,460
我知道这话听起来有点怪
I know this sounds weird...

287
00:18:01,420 --> 00:18:02,860
但我没有更想去的地方了
There's no place I'd rather be.

288
00:18:06,970 --> 00:18:11,210
你这话的语气真...生硬
The way you say that sounds so... rote.

289
00:18:11,720 --> 00:18:12,800
我说不好
I don't know...

290
00:18:15,660 --> 00:18:17,540
这让我怎么回应
What am I supposed to say to that?

291
00:18:20,730 --> 00:18:22,980
我只想知道你好不好  仅此而已
I just want to know how you're doing, that's all.

292
00:18:23,740 --> 00:18:26,400
我只是关心你  坐在我眼前的这个人
I'm just asking about you, this person I'm sitting with.

293
00:18:35,250 --> 00:18:36,910
你想什么呢  汤姆·耶茨
Where'd you go, Tom Yates?

294
00:18:49,000 --> 00:18:50,230
我找你来着
I was looking for you.

295
00:18:50,900 --> 00:18:52,370
看来找得不够用心啊
Not very hard, then.

296
00:18:53,430 --> 00:18:54,670
我得跟你谈谈
I need to talk to you.

297
00:18:57,010 --> 00:18:57,900
好
Okay.

298
00:18:58,830 --> 00:18:59,780
我不干了
I'm done.

299
00:19:02,270 --> 00:19:05,440
我不想再写演讲稿了
With the speechwriting, I don't want to do it anymore.

300
00:19:06,490 --> 00:19:08,820
我想回去做我之前在做的其他事
I want to get back to some other stuff I was working on.

301
00:19:08,820 --> 00:19:13,060
没别的意思  我知道写演讲稿也是写作
No offense. I mean, I know writing speeches is writing...

302
00:19:13,900 --> 00:19:15,700
但这不是我真正想做的
but it's not what I really wanna do.

303
00:19:20,470 --> 00:19:21,520
好
Okay.

304
00:19:24,020 --> 00:19:25,110
你确定
You sure?

305
00:19:26,720 --> 00:19:27,680
是的
Yes.

306
00:19:30,370 --> 00:19:32,010
我们会把你调出去的
We'll transition you out.

307
00:19:33,560 --> 00:19:35,950
但你以后再来就得想好借口了
But you'll need to have a reason to be here.

308
00:19:41,120 --> 00:19:43,530
{\pos(194.7,147.15)}马克·厄舍被任命为总统特别顾问

309
00:19:44,070 --> 00:19:46,190
特别顾问  你逗我吗
Special advisor? Are you kidding me?

310
00:19:46,190 --> 00:19:47,580
有猜测说他已经...
There's speculation that he's already...

311
00:19:47,580 --> 00:19:49,020
这不是猜测  赛斯
It's not speculation, Seth.

312
00:19:49,020 --> 00:19:51,830
人们知道马克·厄舍在某种程度上为我们工作
People know that Mark Usher is working for us in some capacity.

313
00:19:51,840 --> 00:19:54,000
-那还不够吗  -把发布写得好一点
- I mean, isn't that enough? - Clean up this release.

314
00:19:54,010 --> 00:19:56,370
突破党派界限之类的
Uh, reaching across party lines, that sort of thing.

315
00:19:56,370 --> 00:19:58,000
-准备好  以防万一  -当然
- And get it ready, just in case. - Of course.

316
00:19:58,000 --> 00:19:58,990
就这样
That's it.

317
00:20:02,660 --> 00:20:04,780
我知道你不高兴
I know you're not happy about this.

318
00:20:05,080 --> 00:20:06,610
他凭什么能赢得那头衔
What has he done to earn the title?

319
00:20:06,610 --> 00:20:08,160
这不是他赢得什么的问题
This is not about him earning anything.

320
00:20:08,160 --> 00:20:10,130
他已经在接触机密备忘录了
He's already getting classified memos.

321
00:20:10,130 --> 00:20:11,920
她为什么想这样
Why does she want this?

322
00:20:13,730 --> 00:20:14,790
"她"
"She"?

323
00:20:17,640 --> 00:20:19,790
抱歉  我是说副总统
I'm sorry. The vice president.

324
00:20:19,790 --> 00:20:23,500
她想要的是让这个政府成功
What she wants is for this administration to succeed.

325
00:20:23,500 --> 00:20:27,280
而我想要的是你跟他成为朋友  了解他
And what I want is for you to befriend him. Get to know him.

326
00:20:27,290 --> 00:20:28,980
我们要让他以为是他在操控我们
We want him to think he's managing us

327
00:20:28,990 --> 00:20:30,930
而其实是我们在控制他
while we're busy managing him.

328
00:20:33,940 --> 00:20:36,610
她追查弗兰西斯·安德伍德很久了
She has been pursuing Francis Underwood for a long time.

329
00:20:36,610 --> 00:20:38,840
-我不想和她谈  -艾丹
- I don't wanna talk to her. - Aidan...

330
00:20:38,840 --> 00:20:40,430
她怎么知道我在这儿的
How does she even know I'm here?

331
00:20:40,430 --> 00:20:42,870
鲍德温女士是个非常优秀的记者
Miss Baldwin is a very good journalist.

332
00:20:43,850 --> 00:20:46,000
把事情公开对你和我都没帮助
Yeah, going public will not help you, or me.

333
00:20:46,000 --> 00:20:49,860
你就跟她说说  你是怎么操纵美国民意的
You'll tell her how you manipulated the American mood, hmm?

334
00:20:49,860 --> 00:20:52,960
-你是怎么偷走大选胜利的  -那我就完了
- How you helped steal an election. - That would be it for me.

335
00:20:52,960 --> 00:20:57,100
你可是我们俄罗斯联邦的贵客
You're a valued guest of the Russian state.

336
00:20:57,620 --> 00:20:58,820
我想要回我的护照
I want my passport back.

337
00:20:58,830 --> 00:21:01,750
美国护照是绝对保护不了你的
An American passport is the last thing that will keep you safe.

338
00:21:01,750 --> 00:21:03,170
我愿赌一把
I'll take my chances.

339
00:21:07,800 --> 00:21:10,820
这下你要出名了  当个告密者
This will make you famous, hmm? A whistle-blower.

340
00:21:10,820 --> 00:21:12,450
我不想出名
I don't wanna be famous.

341
00:21:14,050 --> 00:21:16,290
但你想要自由
But you do want to be free.

342
00:21:19,800 --> 00:21:21,170
{\pos(69.9,101.7)}传票
由美国国会众议院签发
致  尊敬的泰伦斯·乌麦克
现传召您来众议院纪律委员会出席听证

343
00:21:21,420 --> 00:21:25,800
{\an8}日程安排

344
00:21:24,300 --> 00:21:26,990
你光饭钱就花了一万五
You spent $15,000 at The Capital Grille?

345
00:21:26,990 --> 00:21:27,960
你吃金子吗
What the fuck are you eating?

346
00:21:27,960 --> 00:21:30,870
-这是罗梅洛利用纪律委员会  -这是把柄
- This is Romero using the House Ethics... - It's a liability.

347
00:21:30,870 --> 00:21:32,310
你就不该犯这种错
And you should know better.

348
00:21:33,210 --> 00:21:34,460
这事你怎么没说过  泰瑞
How did you not disclose this, Terry?

349
00:21:34,460 --> 00:21:36,850
我想把他踢出委员会
I want to pull him off his committee assignments.

350
00:21:36,850 --> 00:21:39,790
扔进科学委员会  看他喜不喜欢宇航局报告
Put him on Science. See how he likes NASA briefings.

351
00:21:39,790 --> 00:21:41,220
先缓缓吧
I'd like to hold off on that.

352
00:21:42,030 --> 00:21:44,610
罗梅洛就要成为总统的亲密盟友了
Romero's about to become an ally to the president.

353
00:21:46,200 --> 00:21:47,240
怎么会呢
And why's that?

354
00:21:47,460 --> 00:21:49,960
因为他能查出你的账单有问题
Because he was able to find out about your tab.

355
00:21:50,250 --> 00:21:52,360
因为他从不轻易放手
It's because he's relentless.

356
00:21:52,660 --> 00:21:56,950
因为四年后亚利桑那州35%的选民是拉丁裔
Because in four years, 35% of the vote in Arizona will be Latino.

357
00:21:58,400 --> 00:21:59,720
因为他就是未来
Because he's the future.

358
00:22:03,810 --> 00:22:05,260
就是这么开始的
This is how it starts.

359
00:22:07,340 --> 00:22:08,980
我得回国会去了
I gotta get back to the Hill.

360
00:22:10,400 --> 00:22:11,350
跟你说  道格
You know, Doug...

361
00:22:12,800 --> 00:22:15,810
你我都待得够久  见过换护卫
you and I, we've been around long enough to see the guard change.

362
00:22:16,380 --> 00:22:18,500
之所以会换人  是因为上头那些人
And it changes because the people at the top

363
00:22:18,500 --> 00:22:20,170
忘了自己是怎么爬上去的
forget how they got there.

364
00:22:20,990 --> 00:22:23,210
罗梅洛也想换护卫  道格
Romero's trying to change the guard, Doug.

365
00:22:23,660 --> 00:22:25,340
而我们就是护卫
And we are the guard.

366
00:22:31,340 --> 00:22:33,100
要是乌麦克议员无所隐瞒
If Congressman Womack has nothing to hide,

367
00:22:33,100 --> 00:22:34,610
那他就没什么好怕的
he has nothing to fear.

368
00:22:35,580 --> 00:22:38,330
我们都有要隐瞒的事  罗梅洛议员
We all have something to hide, Congressman Romero.

369
00:22:38,850 --> 00:22:41,400
领导层该换人了
It's time for a change in the leadership.

370
00:22:42,630 --> 00:22:44,860
总统想当你的朋友
The president would like to be a friend to you,

371
00:22:45,420 --> 00:22:47,500
但你让他很难做
but you're making it very difficult.

372
00:22:51,390 --> 00:22:52,770
我们可以保证移民禁令
We can guarantee the immigration ban

373
00:22:52,770 --> 00:22:54,480
下星期就会取消
will be lifted in the next week.

374
00:22:54,490 --> 00:22:56,270
拜托  又来这一套吗
Come on. Are we doing this again?

375
00:22:56,810 --> 00:22:58,650
你开个种族歧视的条件
You offer me some racist gesture.

376
00:22:58,650 --> 00:23:02,720
我怎么  就当死党吗  本来你也禁不住
And I, what? I'm a friend forever? Ban isn't even sustainable.

377
00:23:02,720 --> 00:23:04,060
你最在乎的究竟是什么
What matters to you?

378
00:23:04,060 --> 00:23:05,620
-总统的注意力  -你有啊
- The president's attention. - You have it.

379
00:23:05,620 --> 00:23:08,220
-全部的注意力  -你过分了
- His full attention... - You know, that's enough.

380
00:23:13,480 --> 00:23:15,130
你到底想要什么
What is it that you really want?

381
00:23:15,950 --> 00:23:18,570
我想要医保覆盖率调回原来的水平
I want Medicare coverage bumped up to where it was.

382
00:23:19,930 --> 00:23:22,440
我的选区有不少退休工人
There are retirees in my district.

383
00:23:22,980 --> 00:23:25,380
你见我就只想要扩大医保吗
We're here now because you want a bump in Medicare?

384
00:23:25,850 --> 00:23:27,350
得了吧  议员
Come on, Congressman.

385
00:23:28,610 --> 00:23:30,770
还有两个就职典礼的座位
And two seats to the inauguration.

386
00:23:30,770 --> 00:23:33,120
-就剩两天了  -讲台座位
- We are two days out. - On the dais.

387
00:23:33,150 --> 00:23:36,000
你的算盘完全打错了
You are going about this entirely wrong.

388
00:23:36,010 --> 00:23:40,030
是你主动来找我  是你求我
You came here. You asked me.

389
00:23:40,030 --> 00:23:41,540
我告诉你
I'm telling you.

390
00:23:41,540 --> 00:23:44,000
我就想看弗兰西斯·安德伍德当着我的面
I want to be there when Francis Underwood says to me

391
00:23:44,000 --> 00:23:45,850
宣布提高医保水平
that there will be an increase in Medicare.

392
00:23:45,850 --> 00:23:47,820
只要他一句话  我就是他铁哥们
He does that, I'm his friend.

393
00:23:47,820 --> 00:23:49,190
那我现在就可以代表总统
Well, I think I speak for the president

394
00:23:49,190 --> 00:23:51,180
告诉你这事根本不可能
when I say that's not going to happen.

395
00:23:51,220 --> 00:23:54,430
斯坦普先生  我真的很钦佩你为他做的一切
Mr. Stamper, I really appreciate all the work you do for him,

396
00:23:54,430 --> 00:23:57,930
但你我都知道我的党团在扩大
but you and I know that my bloc is growing.

397
00:23:58,650 --> 00:24:01,430
我只要求他在就职讲话里说句话
All I'm looking for is a line in his address.

398
00:24:03,940 --> 00:24:05,290
两个座位  一句话
Two seats and a line.

399
00:24:06,900 --> 00:24:10,210
-好大的胆子  -我告诉他基本没可能
- The balls on him. - I told him it was highly doubtful.

400
00:24:10,210 --> 00:24:11,860
我可以再回去正式拒绝他
I can get back to him with a firm no.

401
00:24:11,860 --> 00:24:13,310
或者你可以答应他提一句
Or you could give him a line.

402
00:24:13,620 --> 00:24:15,770
他的保证很不可靠
His promises are unreliable.

403
00:24:15,790 --> 00:24:18,860
我了解艾力克斯  我们在康威竞选时见过面
Look, I know Alex. We met on Conway's campaign.

404
00:24:19,160 --> 00:24:20,500
只要他加入  就一定死心塌地
Once he's in, he's in.

405
00:24:20,500 --> 00:24:23,540
总统先生  我们得谨慎决定要给出什么条件
Sir, we have to be very careful with what we're giving away.

406
00:24:23,540 --> 00:24:25,480
他能给政府带来
He's capable of giving this administration

407
00:24:25,480 --> 00:24:26,720
巨大的困扰
an enormous amount of grief.

408
00:24:26,730 --> 00:24:29,200
他只是想让我们对他示好
He's asking for a gesture.

409
00:24:29,200 --> 00:24:31,070
要我说可不止
Oh, I'd say it's a little more than that.

410
00:24:31,070 --> 00:24:34,050
完全同意  他想找帮我们获胜的人的麻烦
I completely agree. He's going after the people who got us here.

411
00:24:34,050 --> 00:24:35,290
他并没有错  对吗
He's not wrong, is he?

412
00:24:35,290 --> 00:24:37,870
有些领导层的人确实该下台了
There are some in leadership whose time has come and gone.

413
00:24:38,430 --> 00:24:41,180
瞧  我是来确保
Look... I'm just here to make sure

414
00:24:41,180 --> 00:24:43,210
你能连任的
your four years turn into eight, but...

415
00:24:43,210 --> 00:24:44,800
但决定权还是在你手上
it's up to you, of course.

416
00:24:46,170 --> 00:24:50,790
他要的不过是两个座位  一句话
But we're talking about two seats... one line...

417
00:24:53,280 --> 00:24:54,490
答应他的要求
Give him what he wants.

418
00:25:02,050 --> 00:25:03,030
艾力克斯
Alex.

419
00:25:04,100 --> 00:25:06,420
蒂尔达  很高兴见到你
Tilda. It's lovely to see you.

420
00:25:06,490 --> 00:25:08,270
-你好吗  议员  -挺好的
- How are you, Congressman? - Oh, I'm fine.

421
00:25:08,270 --> 00:25:10,750
很高兴你们都来了  今天是个大日子
It's good of you all to be here. It's a big day.

422
00:25:10,760 --> 00:25:13,430
要不你们坐我的位子
Listen, why don't the two of you take my seats?

423
00:25:13,430 --> 00:25:14,880
谢了  我们已经被安排在走道旁了
Oh, thanks, but we're already on the aisle.

424
00:25:14,880 --> 00:25:16,080
你们务必收下
I insist.

425
00:25:16,420 --> 00:25:18,870
这样总统说到你想听的话时
You'll be right in the president's line of vision when he...

426
00:25:19,160 --> 00:25:20,510
你正好能与他对视
says what you want to hear.

427
00:25:21,860 --> 00:25:23,460
请吧  我在哪都行
Please. I can be anywhere.

428
00:25:24,700 --> 00:25:25,690
好吧
Okay.

429
00:25:27,080 --> 00:25:28,660
-谢谢你  马克  -别客气
- Thank you, Mark. - Sure.

430
00:25:32,760 --> 00:25:40,310
{\an1}{\pos(40.2,237.15)}弗兰西斯·安德伍德就职典礼

431
00:25:33,140 --> 00:25:37,120
我  弗兰西斯·安德伍德  庄严宣誓
I, Francis J. Underwood, do solemnly swear...

432
00:25:37,120 --> 00:25:40,480
我  弗兰西斯·安德伍德  庄严宣誓
I, Francis J. Underwood, do solemnly swear...

433
00:25:40,490 --> 00:25:42,850
我必忠实执行...
That I will faithfully execute...

434
00:25:42,850 --> 00:25:44,970
我必忠实执行...
That I will faithfully execute...

435
00:25:44,970 --> 00:25:47,990
合众国总统职务
The office of President of the United States.

436
00:25:47,990 --> 00:25:51,320
合众国总统...是的  这一幕似曾相识
The office of Pres-- Yes, here we go again.

437
00:25:51,690 --> 00:25:54,120
国务卿  那时我是想要这个位子
Secretary of State. That's what I wanted.

438
00:25:54,120 --> 00:25:57,850
我只想要这个位子  也是当时许诺给我的
That's all I wanted. That's what I was promised.

439
00:25:57,950 --> 00:26:00,140
而现在  瞧瞧我
And now, here I am,

440
00:26:00,140 --> 00:26:03,800
成了美国总统
President of these United States.

441
00:26:04,800 --> 00:26:06,800
美国人民  这是你们促成的
You made this bed, America.

442
00:26:06,800 --> 00:26:09,030
是你们投票给我的
You voted for me.

443
00:26:11,030 --> 00:26:13,080
困惑吗
Are you confused?

444
00:26:13,140 --> 00:26:15,090
害怕吗
Are you afraid?

445
00:26:15,300 --> 00:26:18,420
因为你以为的梦想成真了
Because what you thought you wanted is now here.

446
00:26:18,650 --> 00:26:21,800
现在你在看着我
And there you are, staring back,

447
00:26:21,800 --> 00:26:23,870
目瞪口呆  一头雾水
slack-jawed, bewildered,

448
00:26:23,870 --> 00:26:26,890
心想这究竟是不是你们想要的
wondering if this is what you actually asked for.

449
00:26:26,890 --> 00:26:31,890
是民主  你们的民主选择了我
This democracy, your democracy, elected me.

450
00:26:32,400 --> 00:26:34,060
如果你觉得走到今天实属不易
And if you think it was hard getting here,

451
00:26:34,060 --> 00:26:37,370
你就能开始明白为了保住权位我会不惜一切
you're beginning to understand what I'm willing to do to stay.

452
00:26:38,350 --> 00:26:40,780
我一眼望向拥挤的人群
I look across at this crowd gathered today

453
00:26:40,780 --> 00:26:43,700
我很清楚他们不是我的支持者
and I know that these are not my supporters.

454
00:26:43,700 --> 00:26:46,240
我看到的是一群脸上挂着微笑
I'm looking at people who are waiting,

455
00:26:46,240 --> 00:26:49,860
等待着自己的机会来临的人
with a smile on their face, for their turn.

456
00:26:50,060 --> 00:26:51,590
那些笑得最开怀
And the most vicious among them

457
00:26:51,590 --> 00:26:55,380
鼓掌最热烈的人  也是其中最阴险的
are the ones who are smiling and clapping the hardest.

458
00:26:55,610 --> 00:26:58,980
权力正如房地产  还记得吗
Power is a lot like real estate. Remember?

459
00:26:58,980 --> 00:27:01,920
-愿上帝助我  -愿上帝助我
- So help me God. - So help me God.

460
00:27:21,270 --> 00:27:24,620
美国人民  我听到了你们的声音
America, I hear you.

461
00:27:25,330 --> 00:27:27,780
我听到了你们所有人的声音
I hear all your voices.

462
00:27:27,920 --> 00:27:31,560
我听到了你们的挣扎  你们的担忧
I hear your struggles, your concerns,

463
00:27:31,560 --> 00:27:36,210
但最重要的是  我听到了你们的希望
but most of all, I hear your hope.

464
00:27:36,260 --> 00:27:40,060
每个人都希望得到机会和保障
Opportunity and security is what we all want.

465
00:27:40,060 --> 00:27:44,080
所以在我上任后的百天之内  我会团结两党
And in my first 100 days, I will reach across party lines

466
00:27:44,080 --> 00:27:47,100
让我的政府  也是你们的政府
and devote my administration, your government,

467
00:27:47,100 --> 00:27:48,700
保障你们的需要
to securing them.

468
00:27:48,700 --> 00:27:51,140
老年人以及他们所依赖的
For too long we have ignored

469
00:27:51,140 --> 00:27:55,170
医疗保险已经被我们忽视了太久
our seniors and the healthcare they depend on.

470
00:27:56,960 --> 00:28:00,940
所以我要致力于改善医保政策
That is why I am committed to fixing Medicare

471
00:28:00,940 --> 00:28:04,850
取得成效前  我不会增加一毛钱预算
before I devote one more dime to the program.

472
00:28:04,850 --> 00:28:07,640
《美就法》只是个开始
AmWorks was only the beginning.

473
00:28:07,640 --> 00:28:11,030
我们得学会不再依赖福利津贴
We have to learn to live without entitlements,

474
00:28:11,030 --> 00:28:14,850
因为我们不是不劳而获的民族
because we are not an entitled people.

475
00:28:14,880 --> 00:28:19,840
我相信你们的每一滴汗水  每一分耕耘
I believe in your sweat. I believe in your hard work.

476
00:28:19,840 --> 00:28:24,030
我今天要向大家承诺的  就是就业机会
And a job, that's what I'll promise you today.

477
00:28:30,460 --> 00:28:31,650
你连一句话都不能给他吗
You couldn't give him one line?

478
00:28:31,650 --> 00:28:34,450
对不忠诚的人我们一个子也不会给
We give no quarter to those that are disloyal.

479
00:28:34,450 --> 00:28:36,990
今天传达的信息不是针对他一人
The message sent today wasn't just for him.

480
00:28:36,990 --> 00:28:40,100
-报仇会燃起艾力克斯的斗志  -我也是
- Alex feeds off of retribution. - So do I.

481
00:28:40,100 --> 00:28:42,570
-他值得你引战吗  -没有中间地带
- Is he worth the fight? - There is no neutrality.

482
00:28:42,570 --> 00:28:45,650
我要求完全的忠诚  不然你就是我的敌人
I expect total loyalty or you are an enemy.

483
00:28:46,700 --> 00:28:48,310
明白了  总统先生
Understood, Mr. President.

484
00:28:53,810 --> 00:28:55,170
你怎么想
What are you thinking?

485
00:28:58,590 --> 00:29:01,280
{\an3}{\pos(374,247)}又称《America》  爱国歌曲
曾是默认的美国国歌

486
00:28:58,590 --> 00:29:01,280
*让人民发出声音*
*Let mortal tongues awake*

487
00:28:58,590 --> 00:29:03,590
{\an9}BGM: My Country, 'Tis of Thee

488
00:29:02,570 --> 00:29:05,170
*让人民畅快呼吸*
*Let all that breathe partake*

489
00:29:05,990 --> 00:29:09,010
*让人民打破沉默*
*Let rocks their silent break*

490
00:29:10,270 --> 00:29:13,070
我就是喜欢这些爱国的东西
I have a soft spot for that patriotic stuff.

491
00:29:23,130 --> 00:29:25,670
请伸开手臂  岔开腿
Please spread your arms and legs.

492
00:29:25,790 --> 00:29:26,740
什么
Excuse me?

493
00:29:27,110 --> 00:29:29,370
否则  别想采访
Otherwise, there is no interview.

494
00:29:35,350 --> 00:29:37,810
还有  请你脱掉外套
And if you would please take off your jacket.

495
00:29:39,560 --> 00:29:41,040
-我是个记者  -我知道
- I'm a journalist. - I know.

496
00:29:41,040 --> 00:29:43,220
我住在伦敦时读过你的报道
I read you when I was living in London.

497
00:29:43,220 --> 00:29:46,250
-我不是间谍  -我知道
- So I'm not a spy. - I know you're not a spy.

498
00:29:46,250 --> 00:29:48,560
现在还有人用那个词吗
Does anyone even use that word anymore?

499
00:29:51,230 --> 00:29:53,670
采访不会在这里进行
So the interview won't be happening here.

500
00:29:53,670 --> 00:29:56,920
-我们说好的  -我们得带你去另一个地方
- Uh, we agreed... - We need to move you to another location.

501
00:29:57,130 --> 00:29:59,470
对不起  你不能用自己的人
Oh, and I'm sorry, you cannot use your own crew.

502
00:30:00,210 --> 00:30:03,370
-这不可接受  -那采访就得推迟
- That's unacceptable. - Then the interview will have to wait.

503
00:30:03,370 --> 00:30:05,160
我们不能信任你们的人
We cannot trust your people.

504
00:30:05,160 --> 00:30:08,150
你也不想让麦卡伦先生有危险吧
And you wouldn't want to endanger Mr. Macallan, would you?

505
00:30:10,350 --> 00:30:12,300
你来吗  鲍德温女士
Are you coming, Miss Baldwin?

506
00:30:19,160 --> 00:30:21,410
你的手机得留下
And your cell phone needs to stay here.

507
00:30:23,490 --> 00:30:24,530
谢谢
Thank you.

508
00:30:33,440 --> 00:30:35,000
支持你的人很多
You have a lot of support out there,

509
00:30:35,000 --> 00:30:37,300
不管总统说了  或没说什么
no matter what the president did or didn't say.

510
00:30:37,610 --> 00:30:39,780
有很多人乐意跟你合作
There are people eager to work with you.

511
00:30:40,720 --> 00:30:41,850
我该告诉你
I should tell you...

512
00:30:43,190 --> 00:30:44,490
我要煽动共和党人
I'm encouraging the Republicans

513
00:30:44,490 --> 00:30:46,680
重启宣战委员会
to restart the Declaration of War Committee,

514
00:30:46,690 --> 00:30:48,110
调查总统
to investigate the president.

515
00:30:49,610 --> 00:30:50,840
这很大胆
That's bold.

516
00:30:51,180 --> 00:30:53,640
-我并不是想打动你  -很冒险
- I'm not trying to impress you with that. - It's risky.

517
00:30:55,790 --> 00:30:57,560
你不想跟白宫的人为敌
You don't want an enemy in the White House.

518
00:30:58,610 --> 00:31:00,150
但你现在在白宫了
But you're in the White House now.

519
00:31:02,210 --> 00:31:03,430
你对我是什么
And you're what to me?

520
00:31:06,020 --> 00:31:07,340
让我帮你吧
Why don't you let me help you?

521
00:31:09,100 --> 00:31:12,500
不非得让其他人输你才能赢
Everybody doesn't have to lose for you to win, right?

522
00:31:16,570 --> 00:31:18,040
肖恩·杰弗瑞斯在吗
Is Sean Jeffries there?

523
00:31:18,800 --> 00:31:21,590
-谁找他  -你是谁
- Who's calling? - Who's this?

524
00:31:21,710 --> 00:31:23,480
我为汤姆·汉默施密特工作
I work for Tom Hammerschmidt.

525
00:31:23,770 --> 00:31:25,820
我不明白为什么把我转接给你
I don't understand why I was transferred to you.

526
00:31:27,020 --> 00:31:30,130
接待员是我的朋友  我认识他  她认识他
The receptionist is a friend of mine. I know him. She knows him.

527
00:31:30,140 --> 00:31:31,920
我已经联系他一天了
Well, I've been trying to reach him all day.

528
00:31:32,540 --> 00:31:34,280
我可以替你捎话
I can take a message.

529
00:31:34,550 --> 00:31:35,730
不用  我晚点再打吧
No, I'll try him later.

530
00:31:35,730 --> 00:31:38,490
他已经不在这里工作了
Look, he doesn't work here anymore, so...

531
00:31:39,670 --> 00:31:42,270
-我是他女朋友  -没事的
- I'm his girlfriend. - That's all right.

532
00:31:43,880 --> 00:31:46,140
-你是谁  -算了
- Who is this? - Don't worry about it.

533
00:31:53,620 --> 00:31:57,100
我是赛斯·格雷森  我有料给你
Hey, it's Seth Grayson. I've got something for you.

534
00:31:57,550 --> 00:31:59,850
莉安·哈维  要被赶走了
LeAnn Harvey, she's being pushed out.

535
00:32:00,600 --> 00:32:02,530
嗯  她出局了
Yeah, she's out.

536
00:32:03,300 --> 00:32:05,330
到了现在  你是唯一
Yeah, well, you're the only one

537
00:32:05,330 --> 00:32:08,280
还得从我这儿听来的人了
that's got me telling you at this point.

538
00:32:09,160 --> 00:32:12,000
好吧  我正在写发布稿
Okay. I'm writing the release right now.

539
00:32:12,400 --> 00:32:13,420
好  再见
All right, bye.

540
00:32:19,320 --> 00:32:21,160
我是赛斯·格雷森
Hey, it's Seth Grayson.

541
00:32:21,570 --> 00:32:22,930
我有料给你
Yeah, I got something for you.

542
00:32:28,370 --> 00:32:30,460
凯特·鲍德温的人本来都准备好了
Kate Baldwin's people were ready to go,

543
00:32:30,460 --> 00:32:32,610
但俄联邦安全局换掉了她的人
but the FSB replaced the crew.

544
00:32:35,130 --> 00:32:36,720
你牙上有东西
You have something on your tooth.

545
00:32:44,610 --> 00:32:46,090
我们知道他们要去哪吗
Do we know where they were going?

546
00:32:46,510 --> 00:32:48,500
不  但他们还在受追踪
No, but they're still being tracked.

547
00:32:48,830 --> 00:32:51,010
凯特·鲍德温就不该跟他说上话
Kate Baldwin was never supposed to talk to him.

548
00:32:51,010 --> 00:32:53,110
-这采访绝不能进行  -我们还有时间
- This interview cannot happen. - We still have time.

549
00:32:53,110 --> 00:32:55,120
不  没有了
No, we don't.

550
00:32:55,680 --> 00:32:56,710
我们得介入
We need to go in.

551
00:32:56,710 --> 00:32:59,210
这可能会产生难以预料的后果
And there might be some unforeseen consequences.

552
00:33:02,720 --> 00:33:04,190
我觉得艾丹不会透露任何
I don't think Aidan would reveal anything

553
00:33:04,190 --> 00:33:07,690
会伤害我  或其他人的信息
that would endanger me... or anyone else.

554
00:33:09,390 --> 00:33:11,210
你跟他的交情有多久
How far back do you and he go?

555
00:33:12,000 --> 00:33:12,910
很久
Far.

556
00:33:14,900 --> 00:33:15,880
仅此而已
That's all.

557
00:33:17,570 --> 00:33:19,350
很遗憾要如此结局
I'm sorry it has to end this way.

558
00:33:20,150 --> 00:33:21,630
我不需要你的同情
I don't need your sympathy.

559
00:33:30,680 --> 00:33:32,070
你快好了
You almost ready?

560
00:33:33,920 --> 00:33:37,730
该死  我找不到我的F了
God damn it. I can't find my "F."

561
00:33:37,730 --> 00:33:39,400
肯定是被人偷了
Someone must have stolen it.

562
00:33:39,400 --> 00:33:41,970
肯定还会找到的
I'm sure it will turn up somewhere.

563
00:33:41,980 --> 00:33:45,430
汤姆  你这身礼服真帅
Tom, you look very handsome in a tuxedo.

564
00:33:46,320 --> 00:33:48,150
我装作撑得起礼服的人
I act like a man that can wear a tuxedo

565
00:33:48,150 --> 00:33:51,710
我突然就撑得起礼服了
and suddenly I'm a man who can wear a tuxedo.

566
00:33:51,710 --> 00:33:53,050
先用这个凑合吧
This should do for now.

567
00:33:53,550 --> 00:33:56,960
-我刚看到艾瑞克·罗林斯来了  -是啊
- I just saw that Eric Rawlings arrived. - Yes.

568
00:33:57,420 --> 00:34:00,430
汤姆  我们过会儿在楼下跟你碰头
Tom, we'll meet you downstairs in just a few minutes.

569
00:34:00,430 --> 00:34:01,310
好
Sure.

570
00:34:04,200 --> 00:34:08,040
斯坦普说  我们一小时后就能有
Stamper tells me that we'll have a bead on Macallan's location

571
00:34:08,040 --> 00:34:09,590
麦卡伦下落的线索了
in about an hour or so.

572
00:34:09,590 --> 00:34:13,300
我刚跟简·戴维斯说了话  她的联络人准备好了
I just spoke to Jane Davis. Her contacts are ready and waiting.

573
00:34:14,830 --> 00:34:16,520
我们能撇清关系  弗兰西斯
We'll have distance, Francis.

574
00:34:16,660 --> 00:34:18,050
我们会欠她的
We'll owe her.

575
00:34:22,700 --> 00:34:25,990
你很帅  很有总统气质
You look very beautiful. Presidential.

576
00:34:26,600 --> 00:34:30,810
你才美  有副总统的气质
You look beautiful. Vice Presidential.

577
00:34:39,880 --> 00:34:43,090
就是这晚  佐伊被杀的那晚
Here we are. The night of Zoe's death.

578
00:34:47,030 --> 00:34:48,600
你觉得那是谁
Who does that look like to you?

579
00:34:49,580 --> 00:34:51,970
一个等列车的普通白人
Just another white guy waiting for the train.

580
00:34:53,280 --> 00:34:54,680
看仔细点
Look closer.

581
00:34:59,100 --> 00:35:03,370
我知道你觉得那是谁  但我不能确定
I know who you think it might be, but... I'm really not sure.

582
00:35:16,290 --> 00:35:17,930
关上门
Yeah, shut that door.

583
00:35:19,990 --> 00:35:22,470
杰拉德·福特的儿子以前会
Gerald Ford's son used

584
00:35:22,470 --> 00:35:25,620
偷偷溜上这些楼梯  去屋顶
to sneak up these stairs to go to the roof,

585
00:35:25,620 --> 00:35:27,510
跟朋友演奏齐柏林飞艇
play Led Zeppelin to his friends.

586
00:35:27,510 --> 00:35:30,450
少年就是少年  不管他在哪
Teenagers are teenagers, doesn't matter where.

587
00:35:30,710 --> 00:35:31,970
这是
And this...

588
00:35:32,850 --> 00:35:36,630
维克多·佩特罗夫摁灭雪茄的地方
is where Viktor Petrov put out his cigar.

589
00:35:40,400 --> 00:35:42,650
那人似乎很不好对付
That guy seems like a real piece of work.

590
00:35:42,650 --> 00:35:44,350
相信我  他的确是
Oh, believe me, he is.

591
00:35:46,100 --> 00:35:47,380
你也是
So are you.

592
00:35:48,390 --> 00:35:50,460
这就未必了
No, I don't know about that.

593
00:36:08,380 --> 00:36:11,120
-你干什么  -对不起
- What are you doing? - Oh, I'm sorry.

594
00:36:20,480 --> 00:36:22,320
你为什么说对不起
And what are you sorry about?

595
00:36:25,280 --> 00:36:28,670
我以为你想要一样  你并不想要的东西
I thought you wanted something that you don't.

596
00:36:31,120 --> 00:36:33,670
你觉得我想要什么
So what is it that you think I wanted?

597
00:36:33,670 --> 00:36:36,800
我们可以再上去  我真的...
We can go back up. I'm... I'm really s...

598
00:36:39,030 --> 00:36:42,700
据说  人体最脆弱的部分
You know, they say the most vulnerable part of the human body...

599
00:36:44,490 --> 00:36:46,380
是喉咙
is the throat...

600
00:36:48,560 --> 00:36:52,620
你要想真正知道自己对某人的感觉
and that you never really know how you feel about somebody...

601
00:36:54,340 --> 00:36:58,820
就需要那人掐着你的喉咙
until they have their hands around your throat.

602
00:37:03,510 --> 00:37:04,780
告诉我
So tell me.

603
00:37:07,760 --> 00:37:09,530
你现在什么感觉
How do you feel now?

604
00:37:23,640 --> 00:37:26,180
恭喜  总统先生
Congratulations, Mr. President.

605
00:37:43,180 --> 00:37:46,860
以免我忘了  莉安·哈维让我跟你打招呼
Before I forget, LeAnn Harvey wanted me to say hello.

606
00:37:48,350 --> 00:37:49,500
她怎么样
How is she?

607
00:37:50,170 --> 00:37:51,180
她要我告诉你
Well, she wanted me to tell you

608
00:37:51,180 --> 00:37:54,330
她没事  她不会有事
that she's... she's all right. She's gonna be all right.

609
00:37:56,620 --> 00:37:58,330
那是什么意思
What does that mean?

610
00:38:00,240 --> 00:38:03,100
她现在  请假了
She's, um, taking a leave of absence.

611
00:38:03,100 --> 00:38:04,350
至少他们是这么说的
Well, that's what they're calling it,

612
00:38:04,350 --> 00:38:05,630
但看来
but it... it seems that

613
00:38:05,630 --> 00:38:08,540
她被赶出政府了
she's being pushed out of the administration.

614
00:38:10,300 --> 00:38:11,700
是她告诉我你在这儿的
She's the one who told me you were here.

615
00:38:11,710 --> 00:38:13,340
叫我来跟你谈谈
Suggested I talk to you.

616
00:38:15,410 --> 00:38:17,470
莉安雇了你  是吧
LeAnn hired you, isn't that right?

617
00:38:17,760 --> 00:38:19,140
家族朋友
Friend of the family?

618
00:38:23,670 --> 00:38:27,240
对  我们这就开始采访了吗
Yeah, um, are we starting the interview now?

619
00:38:27,580 --> 00:38:31,200
不不  我们就聊聊  但应该就好了
No, no. We're just talking. But we should be ready soon.

620
00:38:32,750 --> 00:38:34,070
对不起  我能...
I'm sorry. Can I, uh...

621
00:38:35,350 --> 00:38:38,150
我们开始前  我能单独待会儿吗
Can I just have a second before we start?

622
00:38:38,850 --> 00:38:41,000
-可以  当然  -好
- I think so. Sure. Um... - Okay.

623
00:38:42,170 --> 00:38:44,950
我去...喘口气
Yeah. I'm... I'm gonna need some air.

624
00:38:53,000 --> 00:38:55,790
不  我就回来
No, I just... I just need a second, okay?

625
00:38:56,280 --> 00:38:58,730
好啊  去喘气吧
Of course. Get some air.

626
00:38:58,860 --> 00:38:59,890
好
Okay.

627
00:39:46,350 --> 00:39:47,680
我想借你的手机
I want your phone.

628
00:39:47,830 --> 00:39:50,790
我想借你的手机  拿着
I need your phone. Take this.

629
00:39:52,580 --> 00:39:53,670
一通电话
One call.

630
00:39:55,630 --> 00:39:56,640
就一通
One.

631
00:40:10,050 --> 00:40:11,010
喂
Hello?

632
00:40:11,320 --> 00:40:12,720
莉安  是我
LeAnn, it's me.

633
00:40:15,560 --> 00:40:17,300
天呐  艾丹
My God, Aidan.

634
00:40:17,300 --> 00:40:19,900
我知道你有麻烦了  我们这么办
I know you're in trouble. Here's the plan.

635
00:40:20,050 --> 00:40:22,180
拿支笔  记下这号码
All right. Get a pen. Write down this number.

636
00:40:22,180 --> 00:40:24,430
他是个律师  他可以帮你出国
He... he's a lawyer. He can get you out of the country.

637
00:40:24,430 --> 00:40:26,670
等你到了俄罗斯  我就能保护你
Once you're in Russia, I can protect you.

638
00:40:27,990 --> 00:40:29,200
对不起
I'm sorry.

639
00:40:29,870 --> 00:40:30,830
为什么
Why?

640
00:40:40,780 --> 00:40:43,140
他们还有多久会找到我
How long do I have before they come and get me?

641
00:40:45,090 --> 00:40:46,340
他们就在外面
They're right outside.

642
00:40:46,960 --> 00:40:48,320
如果我跑呢
And if I run?

643
00:40:49,780 --> 00:40:52,590
会有人受伤  你不会想那么做的
Uh, people will get hurt. You don't want to do that.

644
00:40:58,970 --> 00:41:00,410
我喜欢德州
I like Texas.

645
00:41:01,200 --> 00:41:02,620
或许是因为阳光或尘土
Maybe it's the sun or the dust,

646
00:41:02,620 --> 00:41:05,500
但人们打招呼时都会眯着眼
but people kind of squint when they say hello.

647
00:41:05,500 --> 00:41:06,930
我一直喜欢那样
I always liked that.

648
00:41:08,830 --> 00:41:10,420
我就不该走的
I never should've left.

649
00:41:11,590 --> 00:41:13,340
你一直对我很好
You've always been very good to me.

650
00:41:13,620 --> 00:41:15,410
我喜欢你妈妈
I liked your mother.

651
00:41:16,820 --> 00:41:18,430
我很喜欢她
I liked her a lot.

652
00:41:18,820 --> 00:41:20,740
我真的很抱歉
I'm really sorry.

653
00:41:21,110 --> 00:41:22,190
不必
Don't be.

654
00:41:22,970 --> 00:41:25,390
二楼有个守卫是我们的人
There's a guard on the second floor working with us.

655
00:41:25,390 --> 00:41:28,020
他会护送你去个角落  有出租车在等着你
He'll escort you to a corner where a cab will be waiting.

656
00:41:28,020 --> 00:41:29,900
会有人给你开门
Someone will open the door. Just...

657
00:41:31,090 --> 00:41:32,050
上车就行
get in.

658
00:41:32,630 --> 00:41:34,460
你不想念德州吗
So you don't miss Texas?

659
00:41:35,260 --> 00:41:36,330
不  我想
No, I do.

660
00:41:40,960 --> 00:41:42,920
我想获得安宁
I'm trying to find some peace with this

661
00:41:42,920 --> 00:41:43,880
而你在帮倒忙
and you're not helping.

662
00:41:43,880 --> 00:41:46,900
-就再问几个问题  -我要搬走了
- Just a couple more questions. - I'm moving, you know.

663
00:41:47,390 --> 00:41:49,460
-我得到了新工作  -巴恩斯先生
- I got a new job... - Mr. Barnes?

664
00:41:49,590 --> 00:41:52,070
他们将你女儿的死判为意外
They ruled your daughter's death an accident.

665
00:41:52,070 --> 00:41:53,950
我开始有所怀疑了
I am starting to doubt that.

666
00:41:54,070 --> 00:41:57,080
-我们能不能再说一两遍  -知道吗
- Could we just go over one or two more... - You know what?

667
00:41:57,680 --> 00:41:59,350
我不能再这么下去了
I just can't keep doing this.

668
00:41:59,770 --> 00:42:01,550
别再给我打电话了
Stop calling me, please.

669
00:42:10,430 --> 00:42:12,940
采访不会进行了
The interview will not be happening.

670
00:42:13,320 --> 00:42:15,750
会有人护送你回酒店
Someone will escort you back to your hotel.

671
00:42:26,100 --> 00:42:27,170
总统先生
Mr. President.

672
00:42:28,750 --> 00:42:29,980
希望我没来得太晚
I hope I'm not too late to the party.

673
00:42:29,980 --> 00:42:33,120
你正好赶上隆重登场
I'd say you were just in time to make your grand entrance.

674
00:42:33,150 --> 00:42:35,580
这一切开始时  我可没想过
Well, when all this started, I don't think I imagined myself

675
00:42:35,590 --> 00:42:37,310
今晚会跟你一起站在这里
standing here with you tonight.

676
00:42:38,300 --> 00:42:40,700
-再次恭喜你  总统先生  -谢谢
- Congratulations, Mr. President. Again. - Oh, thank you.

677
00:42:42,060 --> 00:42:42,950
我要等你吗
Um, should I wait for you?

678
00:42:42,950 --> 00:42:44,950
不用  舞会上见
No, no. I'll see you inside the party.

679
00:42:47,800 --> 00:42:50,360
那么  罗梅洛如何了
So... how's Romero?

680
00:42:50,360 --> 00:42:52,660
罗梅洛想让共和党人
Well, Romero wants to get the Republicans

681
00:42:52,660 --> 00:42:55,050
重启宣战委员会
to restart the Declaration of War Committee.

682
00:42:55,240 --> 00:42:56,860
好一份就职大礼
What a lovely inauguration gift.

683
00:42:56,860 --> 00:42:58,640
别说你感到意外
Don't tell me you're surprised.

684
00:42:58,640 --> 00:42:59,630
我没有
I'm not.

685
00:43:00,590 --> 00:43:02,340
里面见  去喝一杯吧
I'll see you inside. Get a drink.

686
00:43:07,520 --> 00:43:10,660
你可真美
Well, don't you look stunning.

687
00:43:11,810 --> 00:43:13,650
这一晚很漫长  弗兰克
It's been a long night, Frank.

688
00:43:14,060 --> 00:43:15,350
我得回家了
I need to get home.

689
00:43:15,350 --> 00:43:17,290
得了  赏个脸吧
Come on. Do me the honor.

690
00:43:19,430 --> 00:43:20,500
今晚不行
Not tonight.

691
00:44:41,000 --> 00:44:42,470
道格  打扮得真帅
Doug! Don't you look good.

692
00:44:42,470 --> 00:44:43,790
谢谢您  副总统女士
Thank you, Madam Vice President.

693
00:44:43,790 --> 00:44:45,020
你见到弗兰西斯了吗
Have you seen Francis?

694
00:44:45,020 --> 00:44:46,450
好一会儿没见着了  女士
Not for a little while, no, ma'am.

695
00:44:46,450 --> 00:44:47,370
大家在纷纷离开了
Well, the party's breaking up.

696
00:44:47,370 --> 00:44:49,490
我想让他来跟人道别
I want him to say goodbye to people.

697
00:44:49,490 --> 00:44:51,820
-好  女士  我去找他  -道格
- Yes, ma'am. I'll let him know. - Doug?

698
00:44:53,120 --> 00:44:55,680
我有个问题问你  就一件小事
I have a question for you. Just a small thing.

699
00:44:55,860 --> 00:44:58,740
-怎么了  -你怎么没去看砍头
- What is it? - Why weren't you at the beheading?

700
00:44:59,460 --> 00:45:02,150
-什么  -詹姆斯·米勒被砍头那晚
- What? - The night James Miller was beheaded.

701
00:45:02,690 --> 00:45:04,660
我们都在  我们四个
We were all there, the four of us.

702
00:45:04,660 --> 00:45:07,820
弗兰西斯  汤姆  莉安和我
Francis, Tom, LeAnn and myself.

703
00:45:07,820 --> 00:45:08,940
你怎么不在
Why not you?

704
00:45:10,700 --> 00:45:13,020
你见到弗兰西斯  就说我找他
You see Francis, tell him I'm looking for him.

705
00:45:13,740 --> 00:45:14,700
是  女士
Yes, ma'am.

706
00:45:30,910 --> 00:45:32,540
我以为你迷路了
I thought you got lost.

707
00:45:32,540 --> 00:45:35,120
不  我就想歇歇
No. I just needed a break.

708
00:45:36,170 --> 00:45:38,010
我们要去跟客人道别吗
Shall we bid our guests farewell?

709
00:45:38,010 --> 00:45:39,630
不  今晚还早呢
No, the night is young.

710
00:45:41,580 --> 00:45:42,870
看我找到了什么
Look what I found.

711
00:45:54,310 --> 00:45:56,270
他们要重启委员会
They're restarting the committee.

712
00:45:58,280 --> 00:46:00,360
我以为我们扼杀了那个委员会
I thought we killed that committee.

713
00:46:01,040 --> 00:46:03,000
众议院什么都野火烧不尽
Nothing ever really dies in the House.

714
00:46:03,000 --> 00:46:07,600
只不过关注的人越来越少
It just plays in front of a smaller and smaller audience.

715
00:46:10,890 --> 00:46:13,820
-这事可不小  -我知道
- This is serious. - I know.

716
00:46:15,100 --> 00:46:17,340
但我们还是好好享受舞会吧
But let's enjoy the rest of the party.

717
00:46:45,590 --> 00:46:47,010
你是做什么的
What do you do here?

718
00:46:48,880 --> 00:46:50,160
我为他们工作
I work for them.

719
00:46:54,620 --> 00:46:57,060
总统让我确保你安全回家
The president asked me to make sure that you get home safely.

720
00:46:57,060 --> 00:46:58,200
我给你安排了一辆车
I have a car for you.

721
00:46:58,640 --> 00:47:00,300
我还想多待一会儿
I thought I'd stay a little while longer.

722
00:47:00,300 --> 00:47:02,070
总统明天早上要早起
The president has an early morning tomorrow.

723
00:47:02,070 --> 00:47:03,150
这边请
Right this way.

724
00:47:25,430 --> 00:47:26,970
那个导游
The tour guide?

725
00:47:30,960 --> 00:47:32,980
-什么  -是的
- What?  - Yes.

726
00:47:33,470 --> 00:47:37,270
搞什么  我应该拿那个导游怎么办呢
WTF. What am I supposed to do about the tour guide?

727
00:47:39,650 --> 00:47:42,010
还在媒体接待室  汤姆  不是吧
The press briefing room, Tom, really?

728
00:47:45,890 --> 00:47:47,810
我以为没人会在意
I didn't think anyone would care.

729
00:47:48,730 --> 00:47:52,150
那我是该留下她还是让她走人呢
Well, should I... keep her on or let her go?

730
00:47:52,150 --> 00:47:55,880
她这样做是很不专业的
I mean, it was rather unprofessional on her part.

731
00:47:58,850 --> 00:48:00,440
她很擅长她的工作
She's good at her job.

732
00:48:04,300 --> 00:48:05,380
汤姆...
Tom...

733
00:48:06,560 --> 00:48:08,500
不要对我妻子不忠
don't cheat on my wife.

734
00:48:32,430 --> 00:48:33,670
巴恩斯先生
Mr. Barnes?

735
00:48:36,460 --> 00:48:40,660
你想到别的地方喝杯咖啡吗
Do you want to get a coffee somewhere away from this?

736
00:48:41,970 --> 00:48:43,710
我一直在想你说的话
I keep thinking about what you said.

737
00:48:48,600 --> 00:48:50,350
我在她的东西中找到了这个
I found this with her things.

738
00:48:52,700 --> 00:48:53,880
父亲节那天
It was Father's Day...

739
00:48:54,940 --> 00:48:56,610
是我最后一次跟她通话
the last time I heard from her.

740
00:48:56,970 --> 00:48:58,770
我们不是很亲近
We weren't close.

741
00:48:59,470 --> 00:49:00,940
我很惊讶她会打电话给我
I was surprised she called.

742
00:49:02,260 --> 00:49:04,590
我当然很开心  但是...
I mean, I was happy, of course, but...

743
00:49:06,170 --> 00:49:07,690
我能留着这个吗
Can I hold on to this?

744
00:49:12,980 --> 00:49:14,120
我不知道
I didn't know...

745
00:49:16,230 --> 00:49:17,520
她有麻烦了
that she was in trouble.

746
00:49:20,360 --> 00:49:22,320
当警察问我她是不是有自杀倾向的时候
When the police asked if i thought she was suicidal,

747
00:49:20,430 --> 00:49:24,100
{\pos(139.2,199.8)}崭露头角的记者
在华盛顿特区惨遭地铁事故身亡

748
00:49:20,430 --> 00:49:24,100
{\an8}{\pos(164.1,89.1)}2013年
11月5日

749
00:49:22,320 --> 00:49:24,760
我说  "可能吧"
I said, "Maybe."

750
00:49:29,030 --> 00:49:30,490
我并不了解她
I didn't know her, really.

751
00:49:32,320 --> 00:49:33,510
我也是
Neither did I.

752
00:49:36,970 --> 00:49:38,570
我会调查这个的
I'll look into this.

753
00:49:40,960 --> 00:49:41,890
好
Okay.

754
00:49:43,170 --> 00:49:44,200
谢谢你
Thank you.

755
00:49:57,870 --> 00:50:00,920
政治新闻网  《早安乔》上说了五分钟
Politico. Five minutes on Morning Joe.

756
00:50:00,920 --> 00:50:03,160
发新闻稿真的有必要吗
Was a press release really necessary?

757
00:50:03,160 --> 00:50:04,550
你要去休假
You're taking a leave.

758
00:50:05,390 --> 00:50:06,900
新闻稿上说你要休假
The press release said that you were taking a leave

759
00:50:06,900 --> 00:50:09,020
来考虑一下你的职业选择
to consider your career options.

760
00:50:09,280 --> 00:50:11,760
得看上去像真的才行  你知道的
This has to look real. You know that.

761
00:50:12,730 --> 00:50:14,290
如果他们要和我见面怎么办
What if they need to meet with me?

762
00:50:16,420 --> 00:50:17,750
那他们就会和你见面
Then they'll meet with you.

763
00:50:26,970 --> 00:50:29,020
我可以叫保安护送你出去
I could have security escort you out.

764
00:50:37,960 --> 00:50:40,360
那么既然现在厄舍是特别顾问了
So since Usher is special advisor now,

765
00:50:40,360 --> 00:50:41,930
那你又算什么呢
where does that leave you?

766
00:50:45,510 --> 00:50:48,530
我说过了  如果有需要  他们会给打你的
Like I said, they'll call you if they need you.

767
00:50:53,780 --> 00:50:56,650
我可以成为你的朋友的  知道吗
I can be a friend to you, you know.

768
00:50:57,600 --> 00:50:59,260
不必这样的
It doesn't have to be like this.

769
00:50:59,260 --> 00:51:00,670
我没有朋友
I don't have any friends.

770
00:51:17,000 --> 00:51:20,400
我把他安排在了巴黎的约旦大使馆
I landed him at the Jordanian Embassy in Paris.

771
00:51:21,860 --> 00:51:23,880
我们计划什么时候把他弄出来
When do we plan to get him out?

772
00:51:24,720 --> 00:51:27,370
据我所知  现在还不知道
Well, as I understand it, you don't yet know

773
00:51:27,380 --> 00:51:30,400
麦卡伦先生可能告诉了佩特罗夫总统些什么
what Mr. Macallan may have told President Petrov.

774
00:51:30,400 --> 00:51:33,370
我要麦卡伦回来  越快越好
I want Macallan back here sooner rather than later.

775
00:51:34,020 --> 00:51:37,320
这些事不发生在美国境内会更好些
It's better if these things don't happen on American soil.

776
00:51:37,790 --> 00:51:39,900
是  但我决定了
Yes, but I make those decisions.

777
00:51:39,900 --> 00:51:41,710
当然  总统先生
Of course, Mr. President.

778
00:51:43,280 --> 00:51:44,400
请放心
And rest assured,

779
00:51:44,400 --> 00:51:47,430
这件事是查不到你们身上的
neither of your fingerprints are anywhere near this.

780
00:51:55,610 --> 00:51:57,520
我们怎么处理莉安
So what do we do about LeAnn?

781
00:51:59,780 --> 00:52:04,210
她参与了选举舞弊  天呐
She's been involved in election fraud, for Christ's sake.

782
00:52:05,430 --> 00:52:07,220
她犯了很多错
She's made a lot of mistakes.

783
00:52:08,800 --> 00:52:10,990
是的  但很多人都犯过
Yes, but lots of people have.

784
00:52:10,990 --> 00:52:13,590
话是那么说  但有些人就走到头了
Yes, but some people run their course.

785
00:52:16,680 --> 00:52:18,970
如今真难知道能相信谁
It's hard to know who to trust these days.

786
00:52:19,850 --> 00:52:20,890
可不是嘛
Isn't it?

787
00:52:30,150 --> 00:52:40,150
{\an5}{\pos(193,150)}美国联邦政府内阁包括副总统在内  目前共24名成员
其中负责国家安全的  如国务卿  国土安全部长  国防部长  被认为最重要
此外司法部长  财务部长也是比较重要的位置
而交通部长  农业部长  教育部长等  被认为是相对次要的职位
但因为现任总统特朗普在竞选时承诺
上任后将进行总值1万亿美元的基础建设投资
所以交通部长在现政府中地位较高
现任交通部长是华裔赵小兰  她丈夫麦康诺是参议院多数党领袖
许多媒体认为  特朗普任命赵小兰负责交通部
除了因她在小布什政府任职时  表现优异之外
也可能是希望在基建政策上获得麦康诺的支持

788
00:53:30,150 --> 00:53:40,150
{\an5}{\pos(193,150)}"医保改革"过去八年来一直是美国政治斗争的核心议题
奥巴马的新医保法案在2010年通过后
就一直遭右翼政客及共和党选民的反对
共和党也借此先后夺回了国会两院的控制权
特朗普竞选时  一再承诺上台后会推翻和替代原有的医保法案
但上任后  实际操作却困难重重  现在的替代法案能否通过尚无定数
同时  现有的医保制度在美国社会遇到了大麻烦
2009年推行法案时  奥巴马称法案通过后  保费会大幅降低
但法案施行后  不仅保费年年暴涨  而且由于医保公司亏损严重
在进入2017年后  美国一些地区的百姓已经无法购买"奥巴马医保"
所以替代方案也是势在必行了

